# Manual HTTP probes for the fines module (Phase 4 / Slice 4).
#
# How to use:
#   1. Start the server with `task run`.
#   2. Open this file in JetBrains GoLand/IntelliJ or VSCode with the
#      REST Client extension installed.
#   3. Click the gutter icon next to a request to send it.
#
# Substitute <memberId> / <fineId> after the corresponding endpoints
# return them (or look them up via `psql` against the dev database).

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### POST {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/fines/assessments — fine all overdue loans for a member
POST {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/fines/assessments

### POST {{baseUrl}}/fines/batch/process — assess every overdue loan, auto-suspend when threshold crossed
POST {{baseUrl}}/fines/batch/process

### GET {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/fines — list all fines for a member
GET {{baseUrl}}/members/<memberId>/fines

### GET {{baseUrl}}/fines/<fineId> — read a single fine
GET {{baseUrl}}/fines/<fineId>

### PATCH {{baseUrl}}/fines/<fineId>/paid — mark a fine paid
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/fines/<fineId>/paid
